ogical formations are of outstanding scenic interest, with eroded sandstones forming \u2018forests of rock\u2019. For details see: http://whc.unesco.org/ en/list/179 Tsingy de Bemaraha Strict Nature Reserve (Natural Site, Madagascar). This property comprises karstic landscapes and limestone uplands cut into impressive \u2018tsingy\u2019 peaks and a \u2018forest\u2019 of limestone needles, the spectacular canyon of the Manambolo River, rolling hills and high peaks. The undisturbed forests, lakes and mangrove swamps are the habitat for rare and endangered lemurs and birds. For details see: http://whc.unesco.org/ en/list/494 Vall\u00e9e de Mai Nature Reserve (Natural Site, Seychelles). In the heart of the small island of Praslin, the reserve has the vestiges of a unique natural palm forest preserved in almost its original state. The famous coco de mer, from a palm-tree once believed to grow in the depths of the sea, is the largest seed in the plant kingdom. For details see: http://whc. unesco.org/en/list/261 38 39 40 41 42 43 44 TAKING STOCK: 40 YEARS OF PROGRESS 41 Year of inscription (extension) Area (km2) Criterion (vii) Criterion (viii) Criterion (ix) Criterion (x) COA (2014) COA (2017) Monitoring missions 1982 51,200 \uf061 \uf061 \uf06c \uf06c 2007 2008 2013 2017 1981 14,763 \uf061 \uf061 \uf06c \uf06c \u2013 1978 136 \uf061 \uf061 \uf06c \uf06c 1981 1996 1997 2017 1982 3,300 \uf061 \uf061 \uf06c \uf06c 2006 1982 72,000 \uf061 \uf061 \uf06c \uf06c 1985 1990 1,520 \uf061 \uf061 \uf06c \uf06c \u2013 1982 0.2 \uf061 \uf061 \uf061 \uf061 \uf06c \uf06c \u2013 NATURAL WORLD HERITAGE IN AFRICA: PROGRESS AND PROSPECTS 42 Map label and thumbnail photo Name, type and status, country and short description (usually at time of inscription, abbreviated from http://whc.unesco.org/en/list/, see footnote regarding changes since inscription) Virunga National Park (Natural Site in Danger, Democratic Republic of Congo).", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template"